tionally, for nanoparticles with 1 nm radius of\nthe studied materials, we found validity criteria for the small-particle\napproximation (in which the nanoparticle is modeled as an electric point\ndipole). We believe that these findings contribute to the understanding of\nrotational aspects present in STEM experiments, and might be useful for further\ndevelopments in electron tweezers and other electron microscopy related\ntechniques.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 17 Nov 2022 20:38:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-14"}
